  "text": "This analysis identifies the key components in Kubernetes v1.32.0 that manage API group storage version registration, specifically mapping v1beta1 to v1 equivalents.\n\n## REST Storage Providers with Version Registration\n\nThree REST storage providers define both v1beta1Storage() and v1Storage() methods, implementing the pattern of serving multiple API versions:\n\n1. **admissionregistration** (pkg/registry/admissionregistration/rest/storage_apiserver.go): Defines v1beta1Storage and v1Storage methods that register webhook configurations and validation/mutation policies across API versions.\n\n2. **authentication** (pkg/registry/authentication/rest/storage_authentication.go): Implements both v1Storage and v1beta1Storage methods for managing SelfSubjectAccessReviews and other authentication resources.\n\n3. **storage** (pkg/registry/storage/rest/storage_storage.go): Provides v1alpha1Storage, v1beta1Storage, and v1Storage methods for managing CSI drivers, nodes, storage capacity, classes, and volume attachments across multiple API versions.\n\n## StorageVersion Manager Interface\n\nThe core StorageVersion management system is defined in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storageversion/manager.go. The Manager interface provides:\n- AddResourceInfo(): Records resources whose StorageVersions need updates\n- UpdateStorageVersions(): Updates the StorageVersions in etcd\n- PendingUpdate() and Completed(): Track update status\n\nThe ResourceInfo struct encapsulates the storage version metadata including:\n- GroupResource: The API resource identifier\n- EncodingVersion: The version used for etcd storage\n- DirectlyDecodableVersions: Versions the converter knows how to decode\n- ServedVersions: All versions served by the API server\n- EquivalentResourceMapper: Maps equivalent resources across groups\n\n## ResourceEncodingConfig System\n\nThe ResourceEncodingConfig interface (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go) controls which GroupVersion is used for etcd storage through:\n- StorageEncodingFor(): Returns the serialization format for a resource\n- InMemoryEncodingFor(): Returns the internal representation version\n- SetResourceEncoding(): Overrides default encoding for specific resources\n\nThe DefaultResourceEncodingConfig implementation maintains a map of resource-specific overrides, allowing v1beta1 resources to be stored as v1 in etcd while maintaining backward compatibility.\n\n## Storage Version Registration Chain\n\nThe registration flow follows this chain:\n\n1. **API Server Initialization** (genericapiserver.go InstallAPIGroup): When installing an API group, the APIGroupVersion.InstallREST is called.\n\n2. **API Group Version Setup** (groupversion.go InstallREST): Creates an APIInstaller to register REST handlers and build ResourceInfo objects.\n\n3. **Resource Handler Registration** (installer.go Install and registerResourceHandlers): For each resource, creates ResourceInfo containing:\n   - The EncodingVersion from StorageVersionProvider.StorageVersion()\n   - Decodable versions from ConvertabilityChecker\n   - Served versions from AllServedVersionsByResource\n\n4. **Storage Version Manager Registration**: The built ResourceInfo objects are passed to StorageVersionManager.AddResourceInfo(), which records them for updating the StorageVersion API objects.\n\n## Storage Factory Configuration\n\nThe default_storage_factory_builder.go NewStorageFactoryConfig() defines ResourceEncodingOverrides that explicitly set which version is stored in etcd:\n- coordination.leasecandidates: v1alpha2 (not v1)\n- networking.ipaddresses and servicecidrs: v1beta1 (not v1)\n- admissionregistration policies: v1alpha1 (not v1)\n- storage.volumeattributesclasses: v1beta1 (not v1)\n\nThese overrides are merged with the DefaultResourceEncodingConfig using MergeResourceEncodingConfigs() in helpers.go.\n\n## Storage Cohabitation\n\nThe storage_factory.go AddCohabitatingResources() method links resources that share the same underlying etcd storage, such as:\n- apps.deployments and extensions.deployments\n- networking.ingresses and extensions.ingresses\n- api.events and events.k8s.io.events\n\nThis ensures that equivalent resources across API groups use the same storage location and version encoding."
